title.rendered: Howdy Honey Launches New Western Jewelry Collection

content.rendered:
Online Western Boutique to Offer Western Necklaces, Bracelets, Earrings & More

HUEYTOWN, Ala. - August 18, 2022 - (Newswire.com)

Howdy Honey is pleased to introduce a new line of western jewelry that's now available on their retail website, www.howdyhoney.com.

Western jewelry themes that are featured throughout the Howdy Honey line include:

  • Horses
  • Cacti
  • Conchos
  • Squash Blossoms
  • Cattle Tags

"This new assortment of western jewelry is a welcome addition to our Western Boutique," said Bailey Fayet, lead jewelry buyer for Howdy Honey. "While the squash blossoms, cattle tag and concho continue to be staples in the western category, seed bead is making a strong statement. Due to its intricate detail and creative versatility, seed bead western-themed jewelry has become a favorite with our customers. We've already gotten a lot of interest - particularly in our western earrings - and we're confident this new line of western jewelry will continue to be a big hit."

Howdy Honey currently features well over 2,000 different jewelry products in its Western Boutique. The types of jewelry offered include western necklaces, bracelets, earrings, western rings and pendants.

The website was launched in 2021 and specializes in western gear. In addition to western jewelry, the retail site's offerings include western apparel, home accessories, bags and other items designed to appeal to the cowgirl in all of us.

Howdy Honey is an online retail store and a division of Wholesale Accessory Market (WAM), which has supplied small local businesses since 2000. Headquartered in Hueytown, Alabama, WAM is dedicated to supplying the public with fun and affordable products they can be proud to own.




Press Release Service by Newswire.com
